From: Leon Romanovsky <leonro@nvidia.com>
Date: Sun, 20 Mar 2022 15:50:16 +0200
Subject: net/mlx5: Don't advertise IPsec netdev support for non-IPsec device
Patch-mainline: v5.19-rc1
Git-commit: a8444b0bdd1ae9c437fe6d3ef44f1ba4721c4329
References: jsc#SLE-19253

Device that lacks proper IPsec capabilities won't pass mlx5e_ipsec_init()
later, so no need to advertise HW netdev offload support for something that
isn't going to work anyway.

Fixes: 8ad893e516a7 ("net/mlx5e: Remove dependency in IPsec initialization flows")
Reviewed-by: Raed Salem <raeds@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Leon Romanovsky <leonro@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Saeed Mahameed <saeedm@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/en_accel/ipsec.c |    3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/en_accel/ipsec.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/en_accel/ipsec.c
@@ -532,6 +532,9 @@ void mlx5e_ipsec_build_netdev(struct mlx
 	struct mlx5_core_dev *mdev = priv->mdev;
 	struct net_device *netdev = priv->netdev;
 
+	if (!mlx5_accel_ipsec_device_caps(mdev))
+		return;
+
 	if (!(mlx5_accel_ipsec_device_caps(mdev) & MLX5_ACCEL_IPSEC_CAP_ESP) ||
 	    !MLX5_CAP_ETH(mdev, swp)) {
 		mlx5_core_dbg(mdev, "mlx5e: ESP and SWP offload not supported\n");
